{
  "texts": [
    "Hallucinations occurred in all sections, but most commonly (20%) in the Plan section of the clinical note.",
    "This is an important finding as this section often contains direct instructions or actions to colleagues or patients that can impact clinical safety.",
    "The most concerning hallucinations were the negation type (30% of total hallucinations).",
    "These mostly appeared in the planning section and contradicted what was said during the consultation.",
    "Negation hallucinations can lead to significant confusion and harm, and without the full context of the consultation, readers may struggle to discern which negation is true and which is false."
  ]
}